<item>
            <title>[AMQ-2714] Apache ActiveMQ is prone to XSS Vulnerability</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2714</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cross-Site Scripting Vulnerability exists in Apache ActiveMQ.&lt;br/&gt;
Example:  &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8161/admin/queueBrowse/example.A?view=rss&amp;amp;feedType=&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8161/admin/queueBrowse/example.A?view=rss&amp;amp;feedType=&lt;/a&gt;&amp;lt;script&amp;gt;alert(&quot;ACTIVEMQ&quot;)&amp;lt;/script&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tested on 5.3.1 and 5.3.0 versions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows XP&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
